stylometry:
Goal Seek is a single equation in a single unknown.  The changing cells, also known as the decision variables, can be alterted to change the final outcome.  An example of this would be the cupcake problem I did on our first week of class.  It was for the a cake shop that was trying to figure out how many cupcakes to sell and at what price to make a profit.  By changing the price, the decision variable, the company was then able to figure out what their best possible price would be. 

Data Table can also be known as a "what-if" analysis.  It's what happens to the output when the selected inputs change.  Two examples of a data table would be a one-way table, which is when there are one input to two or more outputs, and a two-way table, which is when there are two or more inputs to one output.
